title.narrative: Palliative Care for People Living with HIV/AIDS

description.narrative: (USAID Southern Africa Regional): This project will ensure that palliative care is underpinned by evidence, widely understood and integrated into all health systems in order to reduce pain and suffering associated with life- limiting and chronic illnesses. This follow-on award will build on the last 5 years of activities which built capacity for palliative care delivery through partnerships with local Ministries of Health (MOH) and national and community based organizations (CBOs) in focus countries. The partner will strengthen those aspects of care and support which retain PLHIV in care, positive living and prevention and develop the capacity of health systems to address emerging needs and priorities related to chronic care, including drug adherence, the long term effects of anti-retroviral treatment and the psycho-social issues that may arise especially among adolescent and young people, working closely with the MOH, other local stakeholders, and CBOs to ensure capacity development and future sustainability.
